contexts.context:
A toy- model used to validate the downfolding replaces the particle- particle- irreducible electronic vertex by the dynamically screened Coulomb interaction within the random phase approximation (RPA), $W_{\mathrm{RPA}}(\mathbf{q},
u) = v_{\mathbf{q}}/(1 - v_{\mathbf{q}}\Pi^{0}_{\mathbf{q}
u})$ with $v_{\mathbf{q}}=4\pi e^{2}/q^{2}$ and $\Pi^{0}$ the noninteracting polarization, and uses a model phonon- mediated interaction $W_{q
u}^{\mathrm{ph}} = -\dfrac{g/N_{F}}{1 + (q/2k_{F})^{2}}\dfrac{\omega_{q}^{2}}{
u^{2} + \omega_{q}^{2}}$ with dispersion $\omega_{q}^{2}=\omega_{D}^{2}(q/k_{F})^{2}/(1+(q/k_{F})^{2})$ and chosen coupling strength $g=0.4$; these modeling choices are employed to produce a conservative, representative test of screening plus phonon kernels in a conventional-metal parameter regime. [23]
